  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 7:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀναβλέψας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐστέναξε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": Jesus looked up in prayer, and sighed or groaned in sympathy. In this case a number of acts, bodily and mental, are specified. Were these peculiar to it, or do we here get a glimpse into Christ’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "modus operandi",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in many unrecorded cases? On the latter view one can understand the exhausting nature of the healing ministry. It meant a great mental strain.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐφφαθά",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", an Aramaic word = as Mk. explains, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "διανοίχθητι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; doubtless the word actually spoken = Be opened, in reference to the ears, though the loosing of the tongue was part of the result ensuing.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
